    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I have a couple of tangentially related questions: \nWhere is `WorldInteractionControllerWidget` instantiated? `git grep WorldInteractionControllerWidget` only shows it in `OpenRA.Mods.Common/Widgets/RadarWidget.cs` under `var controller = Ui.Root.Get<WorldInteractionControllerWidget>(WorldInteractionController);` whose syntax I can't really claim I understand (it looks more like some sort of singleton getter?).\n\nIf there's indeed just a single instance of `WorldInteractionControllerWidget`, should it have \"world\" as a static variable instead? This removes a bunch of parameter-passing to the `WorldInteractionControllerWidget` static methods, such as `SelectActorsOnScreen` and sisters.\n"
  },
