    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Widgets are all loaded via reflection, see `WidgetLoader.cs`. All their config is stored in YAML files which is parsed and applied at runtime.\n\n`Ui.Root.Get`: The `Root` widget is the top-level widget - the whole UI tree is attached to this guy. The method itself finds a widget by a string ID that matches the type. In this case, the radar wants to send some input to this widget so it can move the location of the screen in the world.\n\nStatic variables are a bad idea - if you ever wanted more than one `WorldInteractionControllerWidget` with a different world it would all go horribly wrong. In this case a better idea might be to unstatic the methods so they can make use of the instance variables (but I don't think we need to tackle that in this PR or anything).\n\nHope that helps.\n"
  },
